TY  - JOUR
AU  - Gao, Pengjie
AU  - Parsons, Christopher A.
AU  - Shen, Jianfeng
T1  - Global Relation between Financial Distress and Equity Returns
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhx060
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 31
IS  - 1
SP  - 239
EP  - 277
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This study explores the distress risk anomaly—the tendency for stocks with high credit risk to perform poorly—among 38 countries over two decades. We find a strongly negative relationship between default probabilities and equity returns concentrated among low-capitalization stocks in developed countries in North America and Europe. Although risk-based explanations provide a poor account of these patterns, several pieces of evidence point to a behavioral interpretation, suggesting that stocks of firms in financial distress are temporarily overpriced.Received March 5, 2013; editorial decision December 4, 2016 by Editor Andrew Karolyi.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhx060
ER  - 



